#: src/rust-2018/rustdoc/rustdoc-uses-commonmark.md:1
msgid "Rustdoc uses CommonMark"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustdoc/rustdoc-uses-commonmark.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.25](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.25-brightgreen.svg) for support by default"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustdoc/rustdoc-uses-commonmark.md:5
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.23](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.23-red.svg) for support via a flag"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustdoc/rustdoc-uses-commonmark.md:7
msgid ""
"Rustdoc lets you write documentation comments in Markdown. At Rust 1.0, we "
"were using the `hoedown` markdown implementation, written in C. Markdown is "
"more of a family of implementations of an idea, and so `hoedown` had its own "
"dialect, like many parsers. The [CommonMark project](https://commonmark."
"org/) has attempted to define a more strict version of Markdown, and so now, "
"Rustdoc uses it by default."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustdoc/rustdoc-uses-commonmark.md:14
msgid ""
"As of Rust 1.23, we still defaulted to `hoedown`, but you could enable "
"Commonmark via a flag, `--enable-commonmark`. Today, we only support "
"CommonMark."
msgstr ""
